title: For Sale:  Offers? Wooden Boat - Chris Craft 20' Riviera
postcontent: Last year of production, R-20-782 is the hull number - 288 hulls built in 20' length from 1950-1954. Hulls R-20-501 through 788 were this specific run... that makes this particular mahogany beauty the 7th to the last ever produced. This mahogany wood boat is in project condition with restoration started. Original MBL engine (worth $5,000) is complete and ready to drop in, seat patterns are built and painted ready for upholstery, hardware is there and the trailer is included. Rub rails, chrome, hardware, windscreen, gauges, and a bunch of boxes carefully packed with the small items needed. These desireable and quite scarce, if not rare craft are fetching $30,000 for survivors to $50,000+ for restored boats. I have a bunch of pictures if you will call and request. Will trade for Colt , Ithaca, Remington Rand M1911a1 pistols, Colt Commercial, or other interesting vintage hand guns.
